FAQ - Castle Brands Inc.

























































Press Releases



Home
Press Releases











FAQ


 
Show all 

 How long has Castle Brands been in business? 

	Castle Brands was formed in July 2003 by its predecessor company, Great Spirits Company, LLC, which was formed in 1998.

 What is Castle Brands' fiscal year-end? 

	Castle Brands' fiscal year ends March 31.

 Where is Castle Brands common stock traded and what is the stock symbol? 

	Castle Brands' common stock is traded on the NYSE MKT Stock Exchange under the symbol ROX.

 How can I invest in Castle Brands? 

	You can purchase shares of Castle Brands' common stock through any regular broker or stock purchase service.

 Where are my stock certificates? 

	Most Castle Brands shareholders own the stock in "street name" and do not receive stock certificates. If you would like to request a stock certificate be mailed to you, please contact our transfer agent.

 Who is Castle Brands' transfer agent and how do I contact them? 

	Castle Brands' transfer agent is:

	Continental Stock Transfer & Trust Company
	17 Battery Place
	New York, New York 10004
	Telephone: 212-509-4000

 Does Castle Brands pay a cash dividend? 

	No, Castle Brands has never declared a cash dividend and presently intends to continue this policy.

 Who is Castle Brands' independent auditor?  

	Castle Brands' independent auditor is EisnerAmper LLP.

 Are there any analysts covering Castle Brands? 

	Matthew Gall

	Barrington Research Associates, Inc. 

	 

 Can I request information to be sent to me? 

	Yes, click here to contact us.

 Who are members of the senior management team? 

	Click here to view the members of the senior management team.

 Where is Castle Brands located? 

	Castle Brands Inc.
	122 East 42nd St
	Suite 5000
	New York, NY 10168
	 

 Do you have another question that hasn't been answered?

Please submit your question using the form below.






