Castle Brands Inc. Key Developments

Castle Brands Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended March 31, 2017
Jun 14 17
Castle Brands Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of $22,580,876 compared to $19,963,408 a year ago. Income from operations was of $908,391 compared to $736,875 a year ago. Income before provision for income taxes was of $472,433 compared to $384,368 a year ago. Net income attributable to common shareholders was of $191,350 compared to $426,268 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $2,111,217 compared to $1,422,955 a year ago.

For the year, the company reported net sales of $77,269,131 compared to $72,220,368 a year ago. Income from operations was of $1,904,999 compared to $1,005,547 a year ago. Income before provision for income taxes was of $694,234 compared to loss of $255,858 a year ago. Net loss attributable to common shareholders was of $852,613 or $0.01 per diluted share compared to $2,516,368 or $0.02 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $5,222,989 compared to $3,576,616 a year ago.


Castle Brands Mulls Acquisitions
Jun 14 17
Castle Brands Inc. (AMEX:ROX) is seeking acquisitions. Castle Brands continue to explore strategic relationships, joint ventures and acquisitions to selectively expand their premium spirits portfolio. Castle Brands expect that future acquisitions or agency relations, if any, would involve some combination of cash, debt and the issuance of their stock.


Castle Said To Weigh Sale Amid Takeover Interest
Apr 26 17
Castle Brands Inc. (AMEX:ROX) reportedly working with Perella Weinberg Partners LP on potential sale. Castle Brands is exploring a sale and may draw interest from potential buyers including Constellation Brands, Inc. (NYSE:STZ) and Sazerac Company, Inc., according to people familiar with the matter. Castle Brands is working with advisers at Perella Weinberg Partners LP on a potential sale, the people said, asking not to be identified as the information is private. Castle Brands may also attract bigger rivals, such as Diageo plc (LSE:DGE), and Pernod Ricard SA (ENXTPA:RI), the people said. HeavenHill Distilleries,Inc. may also consider a bid, the people said. No final agreements have been reached and the sale process may not result in a deal, the people said. Representatives for Perella Weinberg, Constellation, Sazerac, Diageo, Pernod Ricard and Heaven Hill declined to comment. Castle Brands didn’t immediately respond to requests.


